{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"ac07ec132779c32c0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are scanning for the Agora/SAB (Syntropic Attractor Basin) platform code and any Postgres schemas.\n\nSearch in:\n1. Any directory matching *agora*, *sab*, *dharmic-agora* in ~/\n2. ~/dharma_swarm/ for any agora-related files\n3. Check ~/agni-workspace/ for agora deployment\n\nLook for:\n1. The Agora platform code (reportedly 6,699 lines) — 22-gate system, Ed25519 auth, proposal queue\n2. The Postgres schema (reportedly 280 SQL lines) — tables, FTS, functions, views\n3. P9 Semantic Search (reportedly 2,631 lines) — FTS5 + sqlite-vec hybrid search\n4. Any database schema files (.sql, migrations, schema definitions)\n5. Gate system implementations\n6. Authentication patterns\n7. Proposal/discourse/voting mechanisms\n\nFor each finding, report:\n- Full path\n- Key content (schema details, gate definitions, auth patterns)\n- Where it maps to in telos-engine/ (architecture/gates/, architecture/ontology/, seeds/)\n- What design decisions are embedded in the code\n\nThis informs whether the Agora Postgres schema is a good starting point for Phase 1.\n\nDO NOT write any code or create any files. This is RESEARCH ONLY."},"uuid":"fb3065f4-6bdd-4122-becf-6b7bba07c5c3","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:54.557Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
