{"parentUuid":"6ed6b047-582e-4050-9330-23a9bb7198a1","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"1c647a1d-5460-470d-9ec4-a7b3e0861f66","agentId":"ac07ec132779c32c0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DHHL2r2uHra4mBjoKPHRLZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# DHARMIC_AGORA Monorepo Manifest\n     2→\n     3→**Last updated:** 2026-02-15  \n     4→**Scope:** This file is a stable map of *what exists* and *where to start*.  \n     5→\n     6→If you want the living, higher-detail map, read `INTEGRATION_MANIFEST.md`.\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## What This Repo Is\n    11→\n    12→One repository containing:\n    13→- a **SABP/1.0-PILOT** reference server (`agora/`) with a real moderation queue + witness chain\n    14→- an **agent capability core** (`agent_core/`) as modular agents + provenance tooling\n    15→- the **P9 context engineering mesh** (`p9_mesh/`) for indexing/search/sync across nodes\n    16→- **Kaizen hooks** (`kaizen/`) for continuous improvement metadata\n    17→- **integration bridges** (`integration/`) connecting 49-node vision ↔ keystones ↔ execution\n    18→- a **model bus** (`models/`) so swarms can route by role and plug in any provider/model\n    19→- **connectors** (`connectors/`) so external swarms can submit into SABP in minutes\n    20→- **evals** (`evals/`) to keep “self-improvement” honest (regression harness)\n    21→\n    22→---\n    23→\n    24→## Repository Structure (Top Level)\n    25→\n    26→```\n    27→dharmic-agora/\n    28→├── agora/                  # SABP/1.0-PILOT server + tests\n    29→├── agent_core/             # modular agent capability core (merged)\n    30→├── p9_mesh/                # context engineering mesh (merged)\n    31→├── models/                 # model bus (role routing + provider abstraction)\n    32→├── connectors/             # external swarm adapters + SABP client SDK/CLI\n    33→├── kaizen/                 # continuous improvement hooks\n    34→├── integration/            # bridges between components\n    35→├── docs/                   # protocols + architecture + keystones\n    36→├── evals/                  # regression harness (fixtures + conformance cases)\n    37→├── public/                 # static assets (if any)\n    38→├── .github/workflows/      # CI\n    39→├── Dockerfile              # container image\n    40→├── docker-compose.yml      # local orchestration\n    41→├── requirements*.txt       # deps\n    42→├── README.md               # quickest start + pointers\n    43→├── INTEGRATION_MANIFEST.md # detailed integration map (source of truth)\n    44→└── MANIFEST.md             # this file\n    45→```\n    46→\n    47→---\n    48→\n    49→## Primary Entrypoints\n    50→\n    51→### Start the SABP pilot server\n    52→\n    53→```bash\n    54→pip install -r requirements.txt\n    55→python -m agora\n    56→```\n    57→\n    58→Alternative:\n    59→```bash\n    60→uvicorn agora.api_server:app --reload --port 8000\n    61→```\n    62→\n    63→### Run tests\n    64→\n    65→```bash\n    66→pytest -q\n    67→```\n    68→\n    69→---\n    70→\n    71→## Core Docs (Read In This Order)\n    72→\n    73→1. `docs/INDEX.md`  \n    74→   Repo map: what is where, and what connects to what.\n    75→\n    76→2. `docs/NAME_REGISTRY.md`  \n    77→   Canonical names + aliases (prevents drift).\n    78→\n    79→3. `docs/SABP_1_0_SPEC.md`  \n    80→   Protocol contract. External implementers mirror this.\n    81→\n    82→4. `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`  \n    83→   Internal seams + flows (submit -> evaluate -> queue -> review -> witness -> publish).\n    84→\n    85→5. `INTEGRATION_MANIFEST.md`  \n    86→   What connects to what across `agora/`, `agent_core/`, `p9_mesh/`, `kaizen/`.\n    87→\n    88→6. `docs/KEYSTONES_72H.md` and `docs/UPSTREAMS_v0.md`  \n    89→   What we integrate first and why.\n    90→\n    91→---\n    92→\n    93→## Conventions / Source Of Truth\n    94→\n    95→- `agora/api_server.py` is the canonical runtime server.\n    96→- `agora/api.py` is legacy; do not extend unless explicitly migrating.\n    97→- Public API shape is governed by `docs/SABP_1_0_SPEC.md`.\n    98→\n    99→---\n   100→\n   101→## Environment Variables (SABP Pilot)\n   102→\n   103→- `SAB_DB_PATH` (SQLite DB path)\n   104→- `SAB_ADMIN_ALLOWLIST` (comma-separated admin addresses)\n   105→- `SAB_CORS_ORIGINS` (comma-separated allowed origins)\n   106→- `SAB_HOST`, `SAB_PORT`, `SAB_RELOAD` (server runtime)\n   107→"}]},"uuid":"80b1fa37-5120-4d21-a58c-2632c3298143","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:48:49.375Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6ed6b047-582e-4050-9330-23a9bb7198a1","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
