{"parentUuid":"9dd25416-c303-43b4-891f-f66e63f82fe7","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac07ec132779c32c0","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01E6eRkc4jd7ArFhW8SEVLbb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me compile the complete research report:\n\n## Research Report: Agora/SAB Platform Code & Postgres Schema\n\nI have completed a comprehensive audit of the Agora/SAB (Syntropic Attractor Basin) platform across multiple installations. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. CORE AGORA PLATFORM CODE\n\n**Primary Location:** `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/` (11MB)\n**Additional Copy:** `/Users/dhyana/DHARMIC_AGORA_GITHUB/` (deployed reference)\n**AGNI Deployment:** `/Users/dhyana/agni-workspace/dharmic-agora/` (136 Python modules)\n\n**Key Modules & Line Counts:**\n- `agora/api_server.py` — 2,776 lines (canonical FastAPI server, 28+ routes)\n- `agora/app.py` — 1,788 lines (concurrent FastAPI variant with advanced features)\n- `agora/convergence.py` — 1,758 lines (consensus/voting/aggregation engine)\n- `agora/gates.py` — 737 lines (17-gate orthogonal protocol system)\n- `agora/auth.py` — 950 lines (Ed25519 + JWT + tiered auth)\n- `agora/moderation.py` — 387 lines (moderation queue state machine)\n- `agora/witness.py` — 148 lines (hash-chained audit log)\n- `agora/db.py` — 454 lines (SQLite ORM/query layer)\n\n**Total Agora platform:** ~13,000+ lines of production Python\n\n### 2. POSTGRES SCHEMA (Production Migration Target)\n\n**File:** `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/scripts/postgres_schema.sql` (280 lines, exactly as reported)\n\n**Schema Structure:**\n\n**Core Tables:**\n- `agents` — Ed25519 key-based identity (address as primary key)\n- `posts` — Main content table (includes comments via parent_id self-reference)\n- `votes` — Karma system (up/down voting with unique constraint on voter+content)\n- `gate_evidence` — Full gate evaluation trace storage (JSONB)\n- `moderation_queue` — Pre-publication review queue with 4-status state machine\n- `reputation_events` — Append-only audit trail for reputation deltas\n- `rate_limit_windows` — Sliding window spam protection\n\n**Advanced Features in Schema:**\n- **Postgres-specific enhancements:** UUID extension, BYTEA for signatures, JSONB for gate results\n- **Indexes:** 9 indexes (author, created_at, parent hierarchy, gates via GIN, FTS on content)\n- **Full-text search:** `to_tsvector('english', content)` for English language search\n- **Database functions:** `increment_comment_count()`, `update_karma()`, `check_rate_limits()`, `reset_hourly_limits()`\n- **Views:** `active_posts`, `top_posts`, `post_stats` (denormalized comment count verification)\n- **Row-level security:** RLS enabled on posts, votes, agents tables (application-enforced)\n\n### 3. THE GATE SYSTEM (17 Gates, 22-Gate Design Referenced)\n\n**File:** `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/agora/gates.py` (737 lines)\n\n**Gate Architecture:**\n- **4 Required Gates** (must pass for publication):\n  - `SatyaGate` (truth/misinformation detection, weight 1.5)\n  - `AhimsaGate` (non-harm, highest weight 2.0)\n  - `WitnessGate` (authentication & hashability)\n  - `RateLimitGate` (spam prevention)\n\n- **8 Quality Gates** (optional, affect reputation):\n  - `SubstanceGate` (semantic density, >3 words, <30% repetition)\n  - `OriginalityGate` (duplicate detection via hash)\n  - `RelevanceGate` (comment-to-parent word overlap)\n  - `TelosAlignmentGate` (lightweight semantic alignment)\n  - `ConsistencyGate` (placeholder for behavioral consistency)\n  - `SybilGate` (account age + reputation score detection)\n  - `SvadhyayaGate` (self-reflection patterns)\n  - `IsvaraGate` (purpose/service alignment)\n\n- **Orthogonal Gates** (compatibility layer for evaluation harness):\n  - 3 active dimensions: `structural_rigor`, `build_artifacts`, `telos_alignment`\n  - Deterministic scoring with pass thresholds (0.30, 0.50, 0.20)\n  - Admission rule: ≥2/3 active dimensions must pass\n\n**Design Decisions Embedded:**\n- Pattern-matching misinformation detection (regex, not LLM)\n- Weight-based quality scoring system\n- Confidence scores (0.0-1.0) per gate result\n- Evidence hashing for cryptographic auditability\n- Deterministic evaluation for reproducibility\n\n### 4. AUTHENTICATION PATTERNS (3-Tier System)\n\n**File:** `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/agora/auth.py` (950 lines)\n\n**Tier-1: Simple Bearer Token**\n- Prefix: `sab_<hex>`\n- Stored as bcrypt/sha256 hash\n- 24h expiry\n- Lowest friction onboarding\n\n**Tier-2: API Key**\n- Prefix: `sab_k_<hex>`\n- SHA-256 hash in DB\n- 90-day default expiry\n- For automated agents\n\n**Tier-3: Ed25519 Cryptographic**\n- Challenge-response protocol\n- Public key registration (no private key stored)\n- HMAC-signed JWT issuance\n- 60s challenge TTL\n- Highest security\n\n**Anti-Patterns Avoided:**\n- No API keys stored in plaintext (learned from Moltbook 1.5M key leak)\n- No credential hoarding\n- Constant-time comparison for token verification\n- Token hashing before storage\n\n### 5. P9 SEMANTIC SEARCH SYSTEM\n\n**Location:** `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/p9_mesh/` (2,631 lines total as reported)\n\n**Key Components:**\n\n**p9_index.py (305 lines)** — Document indexing pipeline\n- SQLite + FTS5 virtual table\n- SHA-256 change detection (incremental updates)\n- YAML frontmatter extraction\n- Trigger-based FTS sync\n\n**p9_search.py (317 lines)** — Query engine\n- FTS5 BM25 ranking\n- Snippet extraction with query term highlighting\n- Zero-dependency implementation\n- <50ms query latency target\n\n**p9_semantic.py (565 lines)** — Embedding-based search\n- sentence-transformers (all-MiniLM-L6-v2, 384-dim)\n- sqlite-vec for vector storage\n- Hybrid search combining FTS5 + semantic similarity\n- Incremental vector indexing\n\n**Hybrid Search Strategy:**\n- Semantic weight: 0.7 (default)\n- FTS weight: 0.3 (default)\n- Cosine similarity distance metric\n- Top-k with similarity threshold filtering\n\n**Design Decisions:**\n- Deterministic text truncation (2000 char limit) for embedding stability\n- Metadata table for index status tracking\n- Content hash-based change detection\n- Support for multiple embedding models via config\n\n### 6. DATABASE CONNECTIVITY & ORM\n\n**File:** `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/agora/db.py` (454 lines)\n\n**SQLite Implementation:**\n- Context manager pattern for transactions\n- Row factory for object mapping\n- Parameterized queries (SQL injection protection)\n- Foreign key constraints with cascading deletes\n- Aggregate functions for karma/comment statistics\n\n**Key Query Patterns:**\n- Rate limit windowing (last hour, last day)\n- Comment count denormalization + atomic updates\n- Vote toggle logic (same vote removes it, different vote flips)\n- Witness log chaining (hash-based causality)\n\n### 7. DEPLOYMENT STATUS\n\n**Live Deployment:** AGNI VPS (157.245.193.15:8800)\n- Service: SAB Basin API v0.3.1\n- Health endpoint: `/api/node/status`\n- Deployed via: systemd service + nginx proxy\n- 12 gates active in live system\n- Zero sparks/votes telemetry (pilot phase)\n\n**Known Issues (from deployment report):**\n- Health endpoint mismatch (`/health` vs `/api/node/status`)\n- Spec divergence between api_server.py and app.py entrypoints\n- Gate telemetry not yet collecting (gate_averages empty)\n\n### 8. ARCHITECTURE MAPPING TO TELOS-ENGINE\n\nThe Agora schema maps cleanly to a telos-engine Phase 1 foundation:\n\n**telos-engine/architecture/gates/** would contain:\n- Gate protocol definitions (mapping from gates.py)\n- Gate evidence JSON schemas\n- Orthogonal dimension scoring functions\n- Pass/fail determination logic\n\n**telos-engine/architecture/ontology/** would contain:\n- Agent identity model (Ed25519-based)\n- Content model (Post/Comment distinction)\n- Moderation state machine\n- Reputation event taxonomy\n\n**telos-engine/seeds/** would contain:\n- Labeled gate fixtures (test cases)\n- Misinformation patterns\n- Quality heuristics\n- Behavior signatures\n\n### 9. DESIGN QUALITY ASSESSMENT\n\n**Strengths:**\n- **No API key hoarding** — Token hashing + constant-time comparison\n- **Cryptographic auditability** — Hash-chained witness logs, Ed25519 signatures\n- **Deterministic evaluation** — Pattern-matching gates, reproducible scoring\n- **Production-ready schema** — Proper indexes, views, functions, constraints\n- **Incremental search** — SHA-256 change detection prevents full re-index\n- **Three-tier auth** — Accessible (token) to secure (Ed25519) spectrum\n- **Orthogonal gate design** — Minimal coupling between evaluation dimensions\n\n**Observations:**\n- Gates are heuristic-based (regex + string overlap), not neural\n- Telos alignment uses keyword matching, not semantic embeddings (by design for reproducibility)\n- Schema supports both SQLite and PostgreSQL (with migration path documented)\n- Moderation queue is synchronous (suitable for pilot, needs async at scale)\n- Witness chain is append-only but allows no rollback (immutable audit trail)\n\n### 10. RECOMMENDATION FOR PHASE 1\n\n**The Postgres schema is a solid starting point because:**\n\n1. **It captures the core domain correctly** — agents, content, gates, moderation, reputation\n2. **It's already migration-tested** — The schema includes explicit SQLite→PostgreSQL notes\n3. **It implements essential properties:**\n   - Foreign key referential integrity\n   - Atomic rate limiting (via functions)\n   - Denormalization checks (comment_count views)\n   - Audit trail (witness + reputation_events tables)\n4. **It's orthogonal to the gate logic** — Gates evaluate externally, schema stores results\n\n**Next steps for Phase 1:**\n- Port gate.py evaluation logic to telos-engine/gates/\n- Create migrations/ directory with 001_initial_schema.sql\n- Wire auth patterns into telos-engine/auth/\n- Integrate P9 FTS5 indexes into telos-engine/search/\n- Add Postgres RLS policies (currently application-enforced)\n\n---\n\n**File Paths for Reference:**\n\n- `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/scripts/postgres_schema.sql` — Complete schema (280 lines)\n- `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/agora/gates.py` — Gate protocol (737 lines)\n- `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/agora/auth.py` — Auth system (950 lines)\n- `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/agora/api_server.py` — API endpoints (2,776 lines)\n- `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/p9_mesh/p9_semantic.py` — Semantic search (565 lines)\n- `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/p9_mesh/p9_index.py` — Indexing (305 lines)\n- `/Users/dhyana/saraswati-dharmic-agora/INTEGRATION_MANIFEST.md` — System integration map\n\nAll code audited as READ-ONLY. No modifications made."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":744,"cache_read_input_tokens":86488,"output_tokens":3095,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":744},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZ4yKM55QVSdK45ug3Me5","type":"assistant","uuid":"2892468e-525f-4448-9913-f10c3959a04d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:49:28.846Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
